cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically abstractive summarization. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes an end-to-end neural model architecture. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as summarization is a common task in this field. The use of unsupervised learning methods suggests it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
